The paper deals with the convergence of the Expectation-Maximization (EM) algorithm for mixtures of linear regressions, which is a problem in machine learning and statistics. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.STAT (Statistics) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the statistical error rate and the use of moment-method approaches, which are relevant to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the paper involves numerical computations and optimization, which are related to cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
